{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 20588, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosangel", "body": "This encounter will be much like the Onyxia's Lair dungeon in the original WoW- basically a few trash pulls and then the boss. However I believe Gruul's lair contains two bosses: Gruul himself and one other.", "date": "2007-01-14T11:18:24-06:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The other boss is [url=?npc=18831]High King Maulgar[/url].", "creationdate": "2007-01-14T21:08:16-06:00", "id": 1003, "rating": 55, "commentid": 20588, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "11502", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Note, they will both drop TWO tokens for Tier 4 armor, come patch 2.1.  This will aid in getting your Tier 4 more quickly.", "creationdate": "2007-05-20T10:44:49-05:00", "id": 298151, "rating": 16, "commentid": 20588, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1497", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Come 2.4, all 25-man raid bosses will be dropping yet another tier token, meaning Gruul, HKM, and others will now drop 3 tokens.", "creationdate": "2008-02-01T16:28:27-06:00", "id": 24640, "rating": 37, "commentid": 20588, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "87017", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 31364, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "17424", "body": "He has around 4-5mill hp. He does a hurtful strike for some decent damage (guess on second highest in threat and melee range).\nevery 30sec he get a buff that increases his damage by 15% and it will stack. => dps race ;)\n\nEvery minute or something he do shatter which knockback people first and when you have 5 debuffs it does upto 9k damage to people around you. damage depends how far they are away. If they are next to you then you do 9k damage, 20yard is like 0 damage. 10yard 4-5k etc.\n\nHard part is the dps and managing the shatter.", "date": "2007-02-05T17:50:47-06:00", "rating": 37, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If there's no one else in melee range, the Hurtful Strike will hit the MT, so keeping both tanks up is essential.  Shatter works like this: Everyone is knocked in a random direction, for a random distance, and given a stacking debuff that slows your movement speed by 20% per stack. It will continue to stack every second until you have 5 stacks, so basically you have 5 seconds to get yourself away from other people. After the 5 seconds he'll do the shatter, which deals damage to everyone within 20 yards or so of you based on how close they are. One person within 10 yards of you will probably ki", "creationdate": "2007-02-05T17:50:48-06:00", "id": 290169, "rating": 24, "commentid": 31364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 64, "username": "devolore", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "\"One person within 10 yards of you will probably kill you.\"  incorrect.  Use the /distance meter that comes with CTRAID - and you can see how many people are in range of you. 0 people is 0dmg, 1 person is 1.2k etc.  You can hide behind the rocks or pillars to avoid the knockback at the start.", "creationdate": "2007-04-03T17:37:28-05:00", "id": 293014, "rating": 12, "commentid": 31364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "30401", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This comment (by Prod) is absolutely incorrect.  Each person in range of you doesn't do a set amount of damage.  It depends on how close in proximity the people are to one another.  I can verify this as I've seen cloth wearers stand on top or right next to each other during a shatter with nobody else around and it will kill both of them.  Read the ability summary at the top of this page or on BossKillers for the correct description of the Shatter mechanic.", "creationdate": "2007-06-23T02:42:09-05:00", "id": 302667, "rating": 10, "commentid": 31364, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "royale", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 50576, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "SilverKnight", "body": "Killing Gruul is all about being spread out and knowing what to do when he throws the players around the room and then uses shatter on them. If you can sort your raid out so they don't bunch together when this happens, you will be able to survive for long enough. Then all you need to do is get your DPS up high enough..", "date": "2007-03-13T13:49:03-05:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I don't think having the raid spread out initially helps much.  He tosses everyone around so much that ranged DPS can end up being thrown underneath Gruul.  The real trick is spreading out as soon as you land after the ground slam, and that really isn't easy.", "creationdate": "2007-06-06T14:45:21-05:00", "id": 300504, "rating": 1, "commentid": 50576, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "40315", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": false, "beta": false}, "responseroles": "272", "responseuser": "Uchur", "response": "", "lastEdit": ["2021-06-30T10:53:10-05:00", 1, "Uchur"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 55465, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "17557", "body": "Hotfixed.\n\nGruul's health has been lowered, and the damage from his shatter ability has been reduced.\n\nGruul should now correctly use his hurtful strike ability.", "date": "2007-03-22T15:07:01-05:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 73736, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "46799", "body": "Can someone else confirm the following:\r\n\r\nWe heard that shatter works like Onyxia deep breath. If you got enough dps he/she won't do it.\r\n\r\nYesterday we raid Gruul lair and we only had 1 shatter in the beginning. After that no shatters.", "date": "2007-04-27T06:52:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The last time we downed him he didn't do anything. It was straight forward tank and spank. I also think that the shatter doesn't work like the deep breath, because our raid-dps was kinda low. In my opinion the shatter timer works like the timers in naxxramas and are a kind of random.", "creationdate": "2007-05-06T11:23:08-05:00", "id": 296423, "rating": 0, "commentid": 73736, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Schnitzel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 79475, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "23311", "body": "Shatter is not like Deep Breath. With high DPS, he will still Shatter. With low DPS, he will still Shatter. On one particularly glorious wipe where a Rogue CoS'd out of Stoned and meleed Gruul, chaining Shatters to both tanks to the point where Gruul sneezed and killed them both, he Shattered while running around whomping the rest of the raid. This was when he had no DPS on him.\r\n\r\nThen again, he Shatters when we drop him to 90% before he even Ground Slams. So, no. Not like Deep Breath. Schnitzel has the right of it; it appears to be kind of a random timer.", "date": "2007-05-08T00:43:51-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 83099, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "spikerz", "body": "His shatter's/grows/aoe silences are all on timers.\r\n\r\nGet bigwigs and they have the timers.", "date": "2007-05-14T18:55:17-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 92154, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "56040_", "body": "Rogues can cloak off the slow effect to move to a safe spot.", "date": "2007-05-28T02:38:46-05:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Note that if CoS is on when the stun arrives, it will be resisted too.", "creationdate": "2007-09-13T08:56:53-05:00", "id": 14977, "rating": 10, "commentid": 92154, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "16856", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes, but even if you CoS outta the stun, you could still get shatter damage from people around you.", "creationdate": "2008-02-20T07:07:41-06:00", "id": 26285, "rating": 7, "commentid": 92154, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "117673", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can't use CloS when stunned, but you can trinket out of it, if you have it when you're doing Gruul's. You'll still take damage even though you trinketed the stun.", "creationdate": "2009-01-06T12:49:32-06:00", "id": 70720, "rating": 0, "commentid": 92154, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fizzles", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 92778, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "13408", "body": "One note for rogues: When Gruul does his knockback. you may CloS out of the Slowing debuff and the \"Stoned\" debuff. this will not only save your bacon alot, but alot of other raid members as well.\n\nEdit: to clarify, his \"Shatter\" spell still appears to detonate you, make sure to keep running out of range of other people.", "date": "2007-05-28T22:43:01-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 94656, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "36540", "body": "As of the present time, Gruul's health is still 3,400,000 -- I don't know why WoWHead's got it at 1,400,000, but that's just wrong. Verified by looking at logs of successful kills.", "date": "2007-05-31T10:57:23-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 98960, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arcticwolf", "body": "As of today's \"patch\" I believe that Gruul the Dragonkiller is now bugged, and will do Hurtful Strike on the 3rd highest melee on aggro list as opposed to the 2nd highest melee on aggro list.\r\n\r\nWhether or not this is intended is beyond me, but I'm sure that not a lot of guilds are happy about this undocumented change... I know ours isn't...\r\n\r\nArcticwolf - Cho'gall", "date": "2007-06-05T20:29:52-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Gruul does NOT attack 3rd on the aggro list in melee range with Hurtful Strike. There are 2 things that could lead one to thinking that:  1) KTM is not 100% correct, so if you are a close 3rd in melee range then i suggest stepping back or vanishing. As a rogue I have previously been killed by hurtful while 10k threat lower than our OT and no. 6-7 on threat.  Ways to combat this: - make sure everyone in the raid is on the same/newest version of KTM. - don't get to close to your guild's OT on threat as KTM is not full-proof.  2) If you are a melee class and run back to Gruul after shatter before", "creationdate": "2007-06-05T20:29:53-05:00", "id": 300580, "rating": -1, "commentid": 98960, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "darrius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confirmed. During my guild's attempts on Gruul, he repeatedly hit the third on the aggro list with Hurtful Strike. Not a fun fight for melee types right now.", "creationdate": "2007-06-06T03:05:09-05:00", "id": 300418, "rating": 1, "commentid": 98960, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "27338", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Was bugged, fixed on 06/07/07:  \"We've reapplied the fix to Gruul that has his Hurtful Strike hitting the 2nd target on the threat list within melee range. Apologies to everyone that had to deal with this bug last night.\"  http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=108236118&postId=1080869862&sid=1#0", "creationdate": "2007-06-07T06:31:00-05:00", "id": 9161, "rating": 18, "commentid": 98960, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dubbill", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 99395, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "18544", "body": "It took us about 5 wipes of getting very aggravated before we looked on the forums and read about the 3rd on aggro list.  We also opened a ticket and a GM said this \"was performing correctly\".  There's a very simple solution to this, just have 2 OT's fighting for the 2nd slot in threat, and it becomes the same fight with 1 less DPS class.  Once we had 1 dps warrior put on tanking gear and join the OT, we beat him on the first try.", "date": "2007-06-06T10:58:18-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 99523, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Arcticwolf", "body": "What our guild did was we had an enhancement shaman (a rogue would work as well) hold 2nd spot in aggro list by using frost shock and not having Salvation on. Having KTM Threatmeter is almost a requirement for this fight now.", "date": "2007-06-06T14:11:15-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 99967, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "10676", "body": "The GM is an idiot. Gruul Hateful Striking the 3rd (or random) melee on the list is - was - an acknowledged bug. Gruul did it previously, it was acknowledged as a bug, it was hotfixed, and with the latest patch, that hotfix was annihilated. Now it has been hotfixed once again.\r\n\r\nForum link to the bug report:\r\nhttp://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=108235375&sid=1\r\nNote on the 4th page there is a link to this forum thread, where a blue post acknowledges the fix:\r\nhttp://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=108236118&sid=1\r\nNow you can go back to bringing 2 tanks instead of having to gimp around with enhancement shaman.\r\n\r\nKTM is not perfectly accurate, but it is DAMN close, and getting better with every version. Most people are not stupid. This was a bug. It's fixed. Go back to your old strats :D", "date": "2007-06-07T06:21:29-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Fixed again, check the WoW Raiding and Dungeons forums. They even apologized.", "creationdate": "2007-06-07T10:29:51-05:00", "id": 300622, "rating": 1, "commentid": 99967, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "18405", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 100749, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "60159", "body": "Any Balance Druids currently fighting against Gruul should take note that the Treants spawned from the Force of Nature ability are not considered to be pets and do produce a Shatter effect. (either that or some of our Gnomes were hiding in them last time...) Since the Treants will never move off of Gruul, this means that your tanks will probably be squashed. \r\n\r\nSimply summon the Treants right after any Shatter in order form them to completely avoid the risk of another one - although they will probably just be one-shot by a Cave-In. :(", "date": "2007-06-08T11:59:27-05:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 101941, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "60893", "body": "Maybe your issue with the Hurtful Strike problem hitting the 3rd person on the list is just as it says above...\r\n\r\n\"As noted above, it is absolutely imperative that the Hurtful Strike Tank be in melee range of Gruul at all times. If Gruul cannot strike the second-highest threat target, he will continue down the list until he finds a target he can strike. This will almost ensure that a melee DPS class will be instantly killed. If there are no other targets in range, Gruul will slam the MT with an extreme spike of damage, almost guaranteeing an instant kill.\"", "date": "2007-06-10T14:51:11-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Had this happen to myself as a fury warrior, intercepting immediately after a shatter..  ALWAYS wait for your 2nd MT to re-engage Gruul after a shatter.  Something I found useful to do during a shatter, specifically as a DPS warrior, is to shift stance to Defensive stance as you are flying and to hit commanding shout (if not given to you by a party member) when you hit the ground.  Helps to mitigate some of the damage of the shatter and give you a bit larger health pool to survive with.", "creationdate": "2007-06-13T12:13:22-05:00", "id": 301377, "rating": 0, "commentid": 101941, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "23740", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 104385, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "37463", "body": "Anyone tried using\r\nhttp://www.wowhead.com/?item=13506\r\n??\r\n\r\n... assuming you can cancel the effect before the 60 secs are up. Might buy the healers some reprieve. Just keep it as an emergency for when you can't get away before the shatter.\r\n\r\nJust posting a brainstorm here ok... so please don't dock my rating or flame me if it's not going to work.", "date": "2007-06-14T16:13:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Invulnerabilities do not prevent you from damaging other people around you, they do, however, prevent you from taking Shatter damage.  For instance, if a Paladin were to use Divine Shield, they would not take any Shatter damage, although they would still damage others around them.  If the Flask would work in much the same way...I'm not sure, because I've never tried. However, I would imagine that it would become quite an expensive means of sorting out a rather managable problem. There should be very few occurances where you aboslutely cannot get out of range of the people around you. Predomina", "creationdate": "2007-06-14T16:13:07-05:00", "id": 302212, "rating": 6, "commentid": 104385, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "60159", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It says invulnerabilites do not prevent shatter damage, so I dont think that would work.", "creationdate": "2007-06-17T15:10:44-05:00", "id": 301899, "rating": 3, "commentid": 104385, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sublime", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just tried using Divine Shield:  I still get the damage, but can move freely before the shatter.", "creationdate": "2007-06-20T17:16:15-05:00", "id": 10095, "rating": 17, "commentid": 104385, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "51171", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 124219, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "matrowop", "body": "Quote \"Gruul's [Earthen Signet] is required for the Serpentshrine Cavern attunement quest The Cudgel of Kar'desh.\" This item is still required for the quest but the quest is no longer necessary for Serpentshrine Cavern attunment.", "date": "2007-07-20T20:31:30-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 127763, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "66777", "body": "it's hp not 2.3 mil , its about 3.3 ...\r\n\r\nneed many dps in raid , watch ur mana , bring pots and damage elixirs with u... and bandage well needed ..\r\n\r\nand you better kill him before about 13-14 th growth   ^ ^", "date": "2007-07-27T12:47:45-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I dont get one thing...  why is it stated as 1.7mil @_@  when in fact it is about 3.3mil #_#", "creationdate": "2007-07-30T21:40:04-05:00", "id": 307035, "rating": 1, "commentid": 127763, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "elitearthas", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "From what I experienced tonight, he was not hitting the second highest on threat with hurtful strike, but rather some random person it seemed.  I could be wrong, but he would turn to me and I'd manage to parry his strike...I'd vanish, and he would turn to me again and rock me for 17k or whatever.  I also saw him go after our ret pally that was no where near the top...rogues and the OT were above him.  Has anyone else seen this happen?", "creationdate": "2007-08-09T23:23:42-05:00", "id": 308132, "rating": 0, "commentid": 127763, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "22897", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 141540, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "63615", "body": "Concerning the Ground Slam/Shatter, druids have a couple abilities that can make them nearly invulnerable to death.  Pop barkskin right after the ground slam, then go to bear form and start running.  As far as I know, there is no type of damage in the game that isn't mitigated by barkskin.  Use it liberally!", "date": "2007-08-21T04:36:15-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "What about fall damage? Now I know cat form has fall damage reduction, but in case you lack mana, or you're a mage that just spell stealed barksin, would that work? My druid is too low level to test at the moment.", "creationdate": "2007-10-02T20:58:28-05:00", "id": 312708, "rating": 3, "commentid": 141540, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Musluk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-08-21T04:47:03-05:00", 1, "63615"]}
