{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 162749, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "86646", "body": "If you are hugging the outer wall prior to a ground slam, you will not be sent flying into the air.  There are also AddOns which which will enable the player to see when Gruul is performing certain actions, but more importantly, to see who would be damaged if a shatter were to occur.  For casters hugging the walls prior to ground slams and being properly spread out, shatters become a non issue.", "date": "2007-10-04T07:45:12-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 163616, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "82099", "body": "Gruul the Dragonkiller\r\n    <Son of Hogger>", "date": "2007-10-06T06:35:43-05:00", "rating": 225, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Gruul the Dragonkiller <[b]Student[/b] of Hogger>  The son of Hogger is Deathwing, everybody knows that :)", "creationdate": "2010-02-01T02:55:52-06:00", "id": 440554, "rating": 18, "commentid": 163616, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "531508", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Chuck Norris <Son of a Bitch>", "creationdate": "2012-11-08T13:21:51-06:00", "id": 596826, "rating": -10, "commentid": 163616, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "GaidinBDJ", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This boss is easily soloable at max level now.", "creationdate": "2013-01-03T12:30:54-06:00", "id": 618820, "rating": -19, "commentid": 163616, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "438040", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 165758, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "dcraftjr", "body": "One good advice is to have a pally with improved lay of hands talent (30% armor buff for 3 min)) use lay of hands when gruul is ~11/12 grows. The extra armor can really help the tank mitigate a lot of damage since silence periods can get hectic.", "date": "2007-10-10T22:59:33-05:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "As a raiding Holy Paladin, I find the idea of using LoH to reduce damage taken for 2 minutes (no, it's not 3), at the expense of my entire mana pool, foolish and irresponsible. If you're MT needs that extra damage reduction that badly, something's wrong.  If you're serious about getting an armor buff for your MT, spec into Improved Devotion Aura and be in the MT and OT's group. It'll provide your tanks with some extra damage reduction, however slight, and not cost you your entire mana pool.", "creationdate": "2008-03-17T11:51:01-05:00", "id": 28461, "rating": 8, "commentid": 165758, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "76224", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If you a a holy pally in Gruuls and do not have many high end mana pots there is something wrong, i spec Tank for PvE and Holy for PVP and i find this quite an ingenious idea.... given that lh will completely restore the tanks health and give the armor buff for 2 minutes. just be sure there is an inervate (druid thing prolly spelled it wrong) onhand and you have your pots cooled down and this trick could save the tank -- not to mention the raid.", "creationdate": "2008-07-02T20:40:47-05:00", "id": 340215, "rating": 0, "commentid": 165758, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "137198", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-01-23T17:04:22-06:00", 1, "dcraftjr"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 170324, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "35268", "body": "If your a druid, just go bear before the shatter (beefs you HP etc etc). As an MT or OT bear tank, feral charge gruul while your in the air, and do remember to save some rage for it (should not be a problem if you have decent hit rating). This is the same trick as you can use on the end boss in underbog that levitates you.", "date": "2007-10-17T09:46:22-05:00", "rating": 21, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Warriors should also stance dance and do an intercept back to Gruul during the shatters.  This helps keep him in one place so he doesn't go running around the room.  Personally I always hit berserker rage after I intercept then swich back to defensive stance in an attempt to regain enough rage for a shield slam/shield block/any other warrior skill because of the rage lost from changing stances.", "creationdate": "2007-11-25T09:31:02-06:00", "id": 19558, "rating": 12, "commentid": 170324, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "NinjaPirate", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You can also pop barkskin when you know you are too close to someone. helps to mitigate the damage and has saved me more than a few times when people land close together.", "creationdate": "2008-10-04T17:39:52-05:00", "id": 49253, "rating": 0, "commentid": 170324, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "64943", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2007-10-17T09:48:20-05:00", 1, "35268"]}
