{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 254074, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sidnal", "body": "So, there I was.....\r\n\r\nFury warrior happily swinging away, 3rd on the melee aggro list (by a safe margin), 2/3 health, and Boom!  Headshot!  Happened 3 times in a row.  What gives?  The MT and OT were in melee range, and I don't see any random player strikes listed in the abilities list above.\r\n\r\n1)  It definitely wasn't cave in, or shatter.\r\n2)  I have no reason to think it was hurtful strike.\r\n\r\nAny ideas?", "date": "2008-03-16T00:36:31-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 257304, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "51698", "body": "Just in case anyone is wondering if you \"need\" a 25-man raid to do this, I can confirm that you can pull this one off with a 20-man raid.\r\n\r\nMy old guild (<The Order of Azeroth>, Nagrand-EU) managed to take him down for the first time tonight with a group of 20 after 3 tries.  When he went down, he was on \"16 grow\".  \r\n\r\nWe have used x2 Warrior tanks and x1 Paladin tank.  We had 6 healers in total - x2 paladins, x1 resto shaman, x1 resto druid, and x2 priests.\r\n\r\nThe tanks kept Gruul in the middle of the room, shifting their position as little as possible when the cave-in kicked in.  All ranged surrounded Gruul and the tanks by forming a large circle.  We tried to keep the x6 healers spaced out.\r\n\r\nThis encounter is easier than High King Maulgar in the sense that it requires less \"control\".  Just watch out for the cave-ins, remember to spread out and stand as far away from each other as possible after AOE knock-back to avoid killing each other with Shatter, keep your tanks on the top of aggro list, and keep the tanks alive, and he will go down.\r\n\r\nIn terms of gear, we were helped a lot by the fact that most of us were more or less fully geared with Karazhan loots and Badge loots, and a few of us had some ZA loots. But some of us still had some blue gears on.\r\n\r\nIf your guild is a small guild that has just enough members to run two Karazhan raid gorups, don't be discouraged by the fact that you don't have 25 people to form a raid group for this.  If you have 20 of the right class, you should give this a try - it's a much more satisfying experience!", "date": "2008-03-22T00:45:57-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If your guild is killing Gruul for the first time, you will most likely need 25 or slightly less people. But when you are progressing, and you come back just for the fun of it, you can do it with a lot less:  Nihilum 15-man (Equipment: T5 and equivalent) http://www.warcraftmovies.com/movieview.php?id=38063 8min 15sec (Growth 16)  Adult Swim 8-man (Equipment: T6 or the best you can get pre-2.4) http://www.warcraftmovies.com/movieview.php?id=71311 10min 35sec (Growth 20)", "creationdate": "2008-04-16T11:40:46-05:00", "id": 31214, "rating": 4, "commentid": 257304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "62991", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "a random roque 5 manned this with not so good quality gear and lot of agility to gain dodge :)", "creationdate": "2008-05-24T00:49:44-05:00", "id": 336130, "rating": 1, "commentid": 257304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "annerajb", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I've just watched it to be done 5-man ^^ And here's a link to the movie :) http://www.warcraftmovies.com/movieview.php?id=75441", "creationdate": "2008-06-19T10:49:48-05:00", "id": 36785, "rating": 3, "commentid": 257304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "149767", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Shards of Existence 5-man (equipment: not even close to full epic) 23min 43sec (growth 30 (then it resetts) http://www.warcraftmovies.com/movieview.php?id=75441", "creationdate": "2008-07-17T19:29:40-05:00", "id": 341885, "rating": 1, "commentid": 257304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "loody", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Boomkin using the hammer of judgement that drops off hyjal trash, and the pally is in t6 shoulders. The rogue may be in a mix of blues and epics to stack for pure avoidance, but the rest of them are t6 geared.   Still really good, but they are far better geared than you let on.", "creationdate": "2008-10-04T17:55:50-05:00", "id": 49255, "rating": 3, "commentid": 257304, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "64943", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-08-24T01:46:12-05:00", 5, "51698"]}
