{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 334482, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "53990", "body": "I don't know if anyone else is currently having trouble with this, but Gruul's Hurtful Strikes appear to be random. My guild has been clearing him for half a year now, so we're hardly new at this. After this last patch, he's been hitting people way, way down the aggro list. I was 7th and I took four in a row until the fifth one finally killed me. Another time, we had an enhancement Shaman and Rogue die from Hurtfuls, so we had them wait [b]a full 30 seconds[/b] - about 1 Growth - after the fight started, and they still got them. \r\n\r\nI'm not sure if it's a glitch right now or a permanent change, but they don't seem to be \"2nd highest aggro in melee range\" anymore.  =(", "date": "2008-07-24T01:41:34-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
