{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 1612295, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bruenir", "body": "Duo'ed this with a BM hunter and Elemental Shammy, both ilvl over 390.\r\nUsed tenacity pet, lots of MD and multishot.  Cleared the hall with AOE and then at Maulgar focused on priest first.  Maulgar gave the pet some grief but overall not too bad once adds were down.  Gruul was easier than Maulgar as no adds to distract.  Move when DBM tells you and avoid the Cave In, the kill was pretty simple.", "date": "2012-01-16T15:06:49-06:00", "rating": -3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 1627355, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "516725", "body": "Duo'ed this last night with a pally in prot off-spec, and me, a destro-warlock with ilevel 330. It's not simple as our ilevels (esp mine) aren't that good, but if you just follow the right kill-order at the first boss, you can manage it. \r\nMake sure you kill the mage first (first from left), since he polymorphs, then the summoner (4th from left incl boss in middle) since he summons and fears, then the healer (second from left). Gruul himself was very easy, it just took a while to kill him.", "date": "2012-02-16T06:50:24-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
