{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1970530, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nynaeve", "body": "Apparently I'm not the only one who noticed the lack of title change, the new Gruul on the Alpha is [url=http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=76877]\"Gruul <The Something>\"[/url].\n\n[spoiler]\nThis is very interesting to me.\n\n[u]Either Blizzard slipped up and forgot to change his title[/u], he's just a placeholder, or the [url=http://wowpedia.org/Black_Dragonflight]Black Dragonflight[/url] will be present in Draenor in this alternative timeline as well (but early?).  Since the dragons [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=19044]Gruul[/url] is renowned for killing are the black dragon followers and children of [url=http://wowpedia.org/Sabellian]Sabellian[/url] ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=22103]Baron Sablemane[/url]), son of and Lieutenant of Neltharion ([url=http://wowpedia.org/Deathwing]Deathwing[/url]), this would seem to indicate that the Alternate Timeline's Neltharion ([url=http://wowpedia.org/Deathwing]Deathwing[/url]) found another way to Draenor to aid the Horde and likely much, much earlier or for a different purpose (or our stories are incorrect and they used some sort of Waygate, or another kind of Portal to get to Draenor, and not the Dark Portal).   \n\nThis could mean that  they ([url=http://wowpedia.org/Sabellian]Sabellian[/url] and his followers and children) will be present on Draenor (and possibly free of the Old God's influence, like our [url=http://wowpedia.org/Sabellian]Sabellian[/url] likely is, due to being worlds away, with the [url=http://wowpedia.org/Great_Dark]Great Dark[/url] and vast [url=http://wowpedia.org/Nether]Nether[/url] between them).  This could also pose issues for [url=http://wowpedia.org/Sabellian]Sabellian[/url], as it could tip [url=http://wowpedia.org/Wrathion]Wrathion[/url] off to his existence in our own timeline. \n[/spoiler]\nBackstory:  \n\nIn our timeline, [url=http://wowpedia.org/Gruul_the_Dragonkiller]Gruul the Dragonkiller[/url] is a massive [url=http://wowpedia.org/Gronn]Gronn[/url] best known for slaughtering and overseeing the slaughtering of droves of members of the [url=http://wowpedia.org/Black_dragonflight]Black Dragonflight[/url] (which is how he obtained our timeline's title), [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=20555]as well[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=21514]as having[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=20216]produced[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=20600]quite[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=18411]a few[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=22199]male[/url] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=22910]children[/url].", "date": "2014-06-06T15:30:44-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-06-12T17:01:10-05:00", 7, "Nynaeve"]}